## Configuration

### Vite Config
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/build-from-scratch#update-configuration-files

### Package.json
- Scripts should use `vite dev` and `vite build` (not custom commands)
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/build-from-scratch#update-configuration-files

## File Organization

### Server Functions Pattern
- **`.functions.ts`** files: Contain `createServerFn()` calls. These can be imported anywhere (client or server). The build system replaces them with RPC stubs in client bundles.
- **`.server.ts`** files: Contain server-only code (database, file system, environment variables). These should ONLY be imported inside server function handlers, never at the top level of `.functions.ts` files.
- Use dynamic imports (`await import('./recipes.server')`) inside handlers to load server-only code
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions

### Execution Model
- All code is **isomorphic by default** - runs on both server and client unless explicitly constrained
- Route loaders are isomorphic - they run on both server (SSR) and client (navigation)
- Use `createServerFn()` for RPC calls that execute only on server
- Use `createServerOnlyFn()` for utilities that should only run on server (throws if called from client)
- Use `createClientOnlyFn()` for utilities that should only run on client (throws if called from server)
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/execution-model

## Common Patterns

### Server Functions
```typescript
// recipes.functions.ts - Safe to import anywhere
import { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'

export const getRecipes = createServerFn({ method: 'GET' }).handler(async () => {
  // Dynamic import of server-only code inside handler
  const recipeServer = await import('./recipes.server')
  return recipeServer.getAllRecipes()
})
```

### Root Route
- Must use `createRootRoute` from `@tanstack/react-router`
- Must include `<HeadContent />` and `<Scripts />` in the HTML structure
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/build-from-scratch#the-root-of-your-application

### Router Setup
- Create `src/router.tsx` with `getRouter()` function
- Use `createRouter` with `routeTree` from `./routeTree.gen`
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/build-from-scratch#the-router-configuration

## Build System

- TanStack Start uses Vite with the `tanstackStart()` plugin
- The plugin automatically handles server function transformation
- Server functions are replaced with RPC stubs in client bundles
- `.server.ts` files are automatically excluded from client bundles when properly structured
- Reference: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/build-from-scratch

## When in Doubt

Always check the official TanStack Start documentation first:
https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react
